---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Thibaut LEFRANCOIS">
  <h2 class="pb-6 text-xl font-semibold italic md:text-2xl">
    full-stack and creative developer
  </h2>
  <div
    class="flex max-w-prose flex-col gap-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-500 md:gap-6"
  >
    <p>
      This portfolio was published far too early, intentionally. I wanted a
      place to write, and Astro was the tool I'd chosen for both the blog and
      the portfolio, so I shipped what I had.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <a href="/blog" class="text-neutral-700 underline">blog</a> is where I document
      what I learn along the way ; short experiments, discoveries, and the web rabbit
      holes that feed my
      <a href="/projects" class="text-neutral-700 underline">project list</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Eventually, those projects will be showcased here in a more creative
      manner. For now, I'm still practicing to get there.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l69ztiHjXb1Q0WuAgiSPmeoh-eoq8Ep9/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-neutral-700 underline"
        >View my CV &rarr;<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a
      >
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
